[[Sergeant/Legends|Sergeant]] '''Bislav Merril''' was a [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Human/Legends|Human]] and a member of the [[Bespin/Legends|Bespin]] [[Bespin Wing Guard/Legends|Wing Guards]] at the time of the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]].<ref name="SEL" />

==Biography==
[[File:Merril2.png|thumb|left|200px|Merril, hard at work]]

Bislav Merril was a veteran of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] on the side of the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]]. He refused to talk about this time with his colleagues.<ref name="SWI" />

Merril was an older man who was known as one of the most tyrannical Sergeants of the Wing Guards; [[Utris M'Toc]] named him a sworn enemy because Merril looked down on his troops with disdain.<ref name="SEL" /> In [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]] Merril and Sergeant [[Isdam Edian/Legends|Edian]] escorted [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], who was frozen in [[Carbonite/Legends|carbonite]], to the [[East Platform/Legends|East Platform]] and delivered him to [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett's]] [[Slave I/Legends|''Slave I'']].

==Behind the scenes==
[[Sergeant/Legends|Sergeant]] Merril was played by [[Alan Harris]] in [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']].<ref name="AlanHarrisMerrilAutograph">{{WebCite|url=http://planetdagobah.com/agCTalanharrisbespingurad.htm|text=Alan Harris-Sergeant Merril Autograph|archiveurl=https://archive.vn/41v5F|archivedate=11-09-2021}}</ref>

Merril's first name of Bislav was first revealed in the [[Rogues Gallery (department)|Rogues Gallery]] of [[Star Wars Insider 148]].

